<br>
Yeah, and if you snuck a peek at your friend's Playboy magazine at age seven, that's just a gateway device to harder and harder porn.  Hell, before you know it you're at the county morgue sodomizing a cold body.  Give me a fucking break.  I know I haven't had the urge to "crack open a cold one", and I do recall seeing a pornographic movie at a friend's party once when I was 15.<br>
<br>
As far as drugs go?  Do it man, legalize them ALL.  Let those with no self-control end up dead, and that's less people for me to have to contend with.  I'm all for it, and not just for the population reducing benefits either.  If I wanted to stay up a few days straight to study, I can go visit my local tweak store and keep a moderate and steady stream of meth going to ace that exam.  If I have problems sleeping, go grab some muscle relaxants and pain-killers.  Ever wonder why doctors are so against the legalization of drugs?  It's not because they give a flying fuck about their patients (some do, but I don't think that the Hippocratic Oath is taken seriously by more than 10% of all doctors)...if they gave a shit they'd not go around leaving surgical instruments, cutting out the wrong organs, and charging you out the ass.  <br>
<br>
It's about <b>control</b> and <b>money</b> here people.  If drugs were legalized, you think that it would just be recreational drugs?  Hell no, people could get the same shit that it takes a doctor to get now.  No more control over patients in many respects, and no more easy $65.00, 30 minute visits where they give the same goddamned antibiotic that they always give out.  Yeah, drug legalization is a scary prospect for doctors because they lose out on a large amount of money.  <br>
<br>
What does this mean to me?  It ain't EVER gonna happen, because as we all know the lobbyists will make sure that congress is well fed by way of the doctors...ultimately by way of you, and your loved ones.  Do this world a service and kick an MD in the crotch...then tell him, "Fix that.  Asshole." spit on him and drive off happy.  *dreams*  Ahhh, if only there weren't such things as assault and battery charges. <p>Faust<BR>
